FBIS4-33472 "drlat109_r_94003" FBIS-LAT-94-109 Daily Report 6 Jun 1994 Peru Police Arrest Ayacucho Shining Path Leader Police Arrest Ayacucho Shining Path Leader PY0606194994 Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network in Spanish 1800 GMT 6 Jun 94 PY0606194994 Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network Spanish BFN [Report by Mario Cueto Cardenas from Huamanga, Ayacucho] [Excerpt] National Police from the 9th Subregion have arrested Comrade Maria, who was in charge of organizing the Shining Path local committee in Ayacucho. Police said Comrade Maria and two other terrorists will be presented to the media in the next few days. Police said these captures allowed the deactivation of future actions against local officials. This is why police distributed special instructions for personal security and invited officials to carry out target practice with short- and long-range weapons. [passage omitted]
